{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-fable-5","id":"msg_01FfR6c9muu8it8sX1VNzg8n","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed and committed as `b267714`.\n\nThe minutes field now uses `(seconds % 3600) // 60`, so `humanize(3661)` returns `'1h 1m 1s'` instead of the inflated `'1h 61m 1s'`. While matching the code to the docstring I also implemented the \"dropping leading zero units\" behavior it specifies — previously `humanize(61)` would have returned `'0h 1m 1s'`, and now it returns `'1m 1s'` (and `5 -> '5s'`, `0 -> '0s'`).\n\nVerified all the docstring examples plus edge cases (`0`, `3600 -> '1h 0m 0s'`), and the test suite passes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":339,"cache_read_input_tokens":30102,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":339},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6156fd94-c7e3-44d1-a025-39377ac0a24a","uuid":"fc5bbba4-6b9d-481d-9baa-72d927340f8f","request_id":"req_011CbtWFj1oKMK7tPy2tzJ27"}
